AppleOfMyIframe
    github.com/premasagar/appleofmyiframe
    
    A JavaScript library for creating & manipulating iframe documents on-the-fly

    author
        Premasagar Rose
            premasagar.com
            dharmafly.com

    license
        opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php

    **

    requires jQuery
        (so far tested only with jQuery v1.3.2)
    
        creates methods
            jQuery.iframe()
            jQuery(elem).intoIframe()
        
    **
    
    contributors
        Alastair James: github.com/onewheelgood
        Jonathan Lister: jaybyjayfresh.com
    
    **
    
    ~2.7KB minified & gzipped
    
    **
    
    Example uses
    
    $.iframe('<p>hello world</p>')
        .appendTo('body');
        
    
    $.iframe(
        '<style>background-color:green;</style>', // or <script/>, <link/>, etc.
        '<p>hello world</p>'
    )
        .appendTo('body');
        
    
    $.iframe(
        '<style>background-color:green;</style>',
        '<p>hello world</p>',
        {
            title:"Jimbob", // document title
            doctype:5, // HTML5
            autowidth:false, // Whether to automatically resize the width of the iframe element, as new content is added and removed from the document body
            autoheight:true // As for autowidth, but for the iframe height
        }
    )
        .appendTo('body');
        
    
    $.iframe(
        '<style>p {color:green;}</style>',
        '<p>hello world</p>',
        {
            title:"Jimbob", // document title
            doctype:5, // HTML5
            autowidth:false, // Whether to automatically resize the width of the iframe element, as new content is added and removed from the document body
            autoheight:true // As for autowidth, but for the iframe height
        },
        function(){ // callback when iframe ready
            alert('iframe has loaded');
            this.body('<p>hello again</p>');
        }
    )
        .appendTo('body');
    
    **
    
    jQuery.iframe
    
        $.iframe(headContents, bodyContents, options, callback);
        
        Arguments
            All arguments are optional
        
            headContents (string)
                * html to be appended to the <head> when the iframe loads
                * e.g. link, style, script tags or elements
            bodyContents (string)
                * html to be appended to the <body> when the iframe loads
                * i.e. the initial body contents
            options (object)
                * e.g. {
                    doctype:5, // HTML5
                    autoheight:false, // Don't resize the iframe when new content is added to the document body
                    title:"Jimbob's Big Day" // document title
                }
            callback (function)
                * function executed on the AOMI 'ready' event, which occurs when the iframe is added to the DOM
    
    
        Returns
            a jQuery collection instance of $('<iframe></iframe>') that has been extended with additional methods => an "AppleOfMyIframe" object
            
    **
    
    jQuery(element).intoIframe
    
        $('#something')
            .intoIframe()
